Sentencas: In this paper, the 3D electrochemical-multiphysics coupling models for the one-cell solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stacks with the parallel flow field and a new parallel-cylindrical flow field have been developed and verified to evaluate their working characteristics.
Titulo: Investigate the effect of a parallel-cylindrical flow field on the solid oxide fuel cell stack performance by 3D multiphysics simulating

Sentencas: Firstly, the 3D model is established based on the realistic component structures including the solid, fluid, and porous components.
Titulo: Investigate the effect of a parallel-cylindrical flow field on the solid oxide fuel cell stack performance by 3D multiphysics simulating

Sentencas: Secondly, the momentum, mass, species, and en- ergy transports, and the electrochemical reactions are coupled to the corresponding regions for carefully considering their effects on the performance.
Titulo: Investigate the effect of a parallel-cylindrical flow field on the solid oxide fuel cell stack performance by 3D multiphysics simulating

Sentencas: The analyzing result shows that a typical SOFC using the parallel- cylindrical rib configuration is concluded to be proper designing in achieving a good stack performance.
Titulo: Investigate the effect of a parallel-cylindrical flow field on the solid oxide fuel cell stack performance by 3D multiphysics simulating

Sentencas: The SOFC stack adopting the new parallel-cylindrical flow field would increase the electric current density by 38 % and improve the reactant distribution uniformity by 60 % than that with the traditional parallel flow field.
Titulo: Investigate the effect of a parallel-cylindrical flow field on the solid oxide fuel cell stack performance by 3D multiphysics simulating
